Types of Healthcare reports:

1. Diagnostic/Laboratory: Blood tests, CT scans, X-rays,etc.
  i. Blood test: To check sugar level, TSH, WBC,RBC count,etc.
  ii. CT scan: Painless, non-invasive test that scans by passing X-rays from various angles for processing.
  iii. Histopathology: To examine slides nad study manifestation of diseases.
  iv. X-rays: To observe injuries and cracks in bones.
  v. MRI: Non-invasive test using magnets and radio waves to observe images of organs, tissues,etc.

2. Clinical: Consultation reports, SOAP notes
3. Procedural/Hospitalisation: Operation, autopsy
4. Medico-legal: Fitness test report,IME
